lcas/farrar-george.html|title=Papers of Sir George Farrar and family|work=ox.ac.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Batten Huddleston|Lt. Col. Henry Batten Huddleston]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] (1864\u20131944), Chief Agent and later a Director of the Burma Railways<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=12|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Nutt (businessman)|Hon. Walter Nutt]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1874\u20131940), managing director of [[Straits Trading Company|The Straits Trading Company]] (1918\u201321)<ref>1891 England Census, Boarder at Bedford Modern School</ref>\n* [[Noel Mobbs|Sir Noel Mobbs]] [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1878\u20131959), founder of [[Slough Estates]] and [[High sheriff]] of [[Buckinghamshire]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[E.E. Blake]] (1879\u20131961), Chairman of [[Eastman Kodak|Kodak UK]]<ref name=\"mocavo.co.uk\"/>\n* [[William Alfred Pickwoad|William Pickwoad]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1886\u20131975), prominent in South America's railway industry. Founding director of the [[Central Bank of Bolivia]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/> \n* [[W. T. Godber]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131981), authority on agriculture and [[agricultural engineering]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr W.T. Godber'', 24 April 1981, p.14</ref>\n* [[Sir Henry Cecil Johnson]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (1906\u20131988), chairman of the [[British Railways Board]] (1968\u201371)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Alastair George MacKenzie]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1915\u20131989), prominent figure in [[Southeast Asia|South East Asian]] insurance during the 1960s and 1970s<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=kn4uAQAAIAAJ&q=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern&dq=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern|title=Who's who in Malaysia and Guide to Singapore|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1967}}</ref>\n* [[Francis Coulson]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (1919\u20131998), [[chef]] and hotelier<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/obituary-francis-coulson-1148567.html|title=Obituary: Francis Coulson|work=The Independent|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=1998-03-06}}</ref>\n* [[Edward Roy Kent]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1920\u20132009), estate owner and agriculturalist in the [[Caribbean]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Ray Daniels|Lt.-Col. Ray Daniels]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1923\u20132003), Chief Executive of the [[William Press Group]]<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1438488/Ray-Daniels.html|title=Ray Daniels|date=11 August 2003|work=Telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Max Wideman]] (born 1927), expert in [[project management]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxwideman.com/contact.htm|title=Expert Project Management \u2013 Contact Information \u2013 Max Wideman|work=maxwideman.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sir Anthony Hartwell, 6th Baronet]] (born 1940), [[Master mariner]] and [[Marine surveyor]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/659/%28Francis%29-Anthony-Charles-Peter-HARTWELL |title=Sir Anthony Hartwell, Bt Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today |work=debretts.com |accessdate=30 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111190252/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/659/%28Francis%29-Anthony-Charles-Peter-HARTWELL |archivedate=11 November 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[John Quenby]] (born 1941), Chief Executive of the [[Motor Sports Association|RAC Motor Sports Association]] (1990\u20132001)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/2956/John-Richard-QUENBY|title=John Quenby, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=1 March 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150221180117/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/2956/John-Richard-QUENBY|archivedate=21 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Andrew Stuart Winckler]] (1949\u20132007), Chief Executive of the [[Financial Services Authority]] (1996\u201398)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Adrian Penfold]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal Town Planning Institute|MRTPI]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (born 1952), Head of Planning at [[British Land]], adviser to the UK Government<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/25466/Adrian-Philip-PENFOLD |title=Adrian Penfold, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today |work=debretts.com |accessdate=25 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705010128/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/25466/Adrian-Philip-PENFOLD |archivedate=5 July 2015 }}</ref>\n* [[Graham Clive Watts]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Chartered Management Institute|MCMI]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] [[Royal Institute of British Architects|FRIBA]] (born 1956), Chief Executive of the [[Construction Industry Council]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Richard Bradbury (retailer)|Richard Bradbury]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (born 1956), Chief Executive of [[River Island]] (2008\u201311), director of [[Boden (clothing)|Boden]] (2012\u2013)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Steve Melton (businessman)|Steve Melton]] (born 1962), Chief Executive of [[Circle Health Ltd]]<ref>Interview in [[The Sunday Times]], Business Section, 15 February 2015</ref>\n* [[Nick Blofeld]] (born 1964), managing director of [[Epsom Downs Racecourse]] (2007\u201309), Chief Executive of [[Bath Rugby]] (2009\u201314)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Marcus Weldon]] (born 1968), 13th President of [[Bell Labs]]\n* [[Johnny Luk]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (born 1991), entrepreneur and Conservative Party candidate<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.neehao.co.uk/2014/08/interview-with-nacue-ceo-johnny-luk/|title=Interview with NACUE CEO Johnny Luk \u2013 Nee Hao Magazine}}</ref>\n\n==Journalism==\n\n* [[William Fairbridge]] [[Justice of the Peace|JP]] (1863\u20131943), founder of the ''[[Rhodesia Herald]]'' and the ''[[The Chronicle (Zimbabwe)|Bulawayo Chronicle]]'', first mayor of [[Harare|Salisbury]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. li.</ref>\n* [[Leonard Dudeney]] (1875\u20131956), newspaper editor (''[[North China Daily News]]'') and parliamentary correspondent (''[[Daily Express]]'' and ''[[Daily Sketch]]'')<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=r9RkAAAAMAAJ&dq=dudeney+bedford+modern&q=dudeney+Bedford|title=Who was who among English and European authors, 1931\u20131949|accessdate=19 June 2015|year=1978|last1=Pine|first1=L. G.|last2=Martell|first2=Edward|last3=Lawrence|first3=Alberta}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. Leonard Dudeney'', 7 January 1957, p.10</ref>\n* [[A. P. Ager|Albert Powtrill Ager]] (1876\u20131956), editor, manager and publisher of ''[[The Straits Times]]''<ref name=\"archive.org\">{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/whoswhoinfareast00hongrich/whoswhoinfareast00hongrich_djvu.txt|title=Full text of \"Who's who in the Far East, 1906-7, June\"|work=archive.org|accessdate=4 August 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Lindsay Bashford]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1881\u20131921), Literary Editor of the ''[[Daily Mail]]''<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[George Matthews (journalist)|George Matthews]] (1917\u20132005), leading communist and editor of the ''[[Daily Worker (UK)|Daily Worker]]''/''[[Morning Star (UK newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' from 1959\u20131974<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Eric Litchfield]] (1920\u20131982), sports editor of ''[[The Rand Daily Mail]]'' (1956\u20131970), the ''[[Cape Times]]'' (1970\u201382) and author<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Jon Akass]] (1933\u20131990), [[Fleet Street]] columnist<ref>Old Bedford Modernians, Eagle News, Number 62, January 1991, p.40</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Guardian]]'', ''Write after lunch'', by [[Keith Waterhouse]], Tuesday June 5, 1990</ref>\n* [[Nicholas Lloyd|Sir Nicholas Lloyd]] (born 1942), newspaper editor, ''[[News of the World]]'' (1984) and the ''[[Daily Express]]'' (1986\u201395)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Michael Toner (journalist)|Michael Toner]] (born 1944), [[List of leader writers|leader writer]] at the ''[[Sunday Express]]'' and ''[[Daily Mail]]''. Author and novelist<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Christopher Wilson (Royal Biographer)|Christopher Wilson]] (born 1947), journalist and [[British Royal Family|Royal]] [[List of biographers|biographer]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Nicholas Shaxson]] (born 1966), author, journalist and associate fellow of [[Chatham House]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chathamhouse.org/about-us/directory/70632#|title=Nicholas Shaxson|work=Chatham House|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Anderson (journalist)|Ben Anderson]] (born 1975), television reporter and writer (''[[Holidays in the Axis of Evil]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Law==\n[[File:William Robert Bousfield.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[William Robert Bousfield|W. R. Bousfield]]]]\n* [[William Robert Bousfield]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1854\u20131943)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Sir William Tudball]] (1866\u20131943). [[Puisne judge]] of the High Court of [[Allahabad]] (1909\u20131922)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir William Tudball'', 24 April 1939, p.14</ref>\n* [[Sidney Abrahams|Sir Sidney Abrahams]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] (1885\u20131957), Chief Justice of [[Tanganyika]]