ica: Supplement to the Who's Who of Southern Africa.  Combined Publishers, 1967</ref>\n* [[Victor Yarnell]] (1919\u20132005), American politician, [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[Mayor of Reading, Pennsylvania]] (1968\u20131972)<ref>http://www.house.state.pa.us/BMC/Bios/PDF/1603.PDF</ref>\n* [[Ian Arthur Naunton Cook|Colonel Ian Cook]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1934\u20131994), Commander of the [[Law enforcement in Vanuatu|Vanuatu Mobile Police Force]] (1980\u201384)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Malcolm Geoffrey Hilson]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 1942), [[High Commissioner]] of [[Vanuatu]] (1997\u20132000)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Paul Reddicliffe]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 1945), British Ambassador to the Kingdom of [[Cambodia]] (1994\u20131997)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\n==Religion==\n[[File:Bishops at Walsingham (4666974401) (Tony Robinson cropped).jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Tony Robinson (bishop)|Tony Robinson]]]]\n* [[William Edward Toll|The Rt. Rev. William Toll]] (1843\u20131915), [[Suffragan bishop]] of the [[Episcopal Diocese of Chicago]] (1911\u201315)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Thomas Blyth (cleric)|Canon Thomas Blyth]] [[Doctor of Divinity|DD]] (1844\u20131913), author and [[Commissary]] to the [[Anglican Diocese of Ottawa|Archbishop of Ottawa]] and [[Diocese of Niagara|Bishops of Niagara]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Canon T.A. Blyth'', 22 July 1913, p.11</ref>\n* [[Henry Arthur Lester|The Rev. H.A. Lester]] [[Master of Arts (Oxbridge and Dublin)|MA]] (1873\u20131922), theologian, director of the [[Bishop of London|Bishop of London's]] Sunday School Council (1911\u20131922)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''The Rev H. A. Lester'', 26 July 1922, p.16</ref><ref>{{Cite book |doi=10.1093/ww/9780199540884.013.U199273 |chapter=Lester, Rev. Henry Arthur, (died 24 July 1922), Director, Bishop of London's Sunday School Council |title=Who Was Who |year=2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|