.com/Whos-Who-Men-and-Women-of-the-Time-1935/107381/2979#2436|title=Whos Who, Men and Women of the Time, 1935|work=Mocavo|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[James Meldrum Knox|Lt.-Col. James Knox]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] (1878\u20131918), Battalion Commander, [[Royal Warwickshire Regiment]], 1915\u201318<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School''(Bedford, no date), p. 72</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Lieutenant-Colonel J.M. Knox D.S.O., Royal Warwick Regiment'', 3 October 1918, p.3</ref>\n* [[Herbert Thomas Dobbin|Brigadier-General Herbert Dobbin]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131946), [[Colonel-Commandant]], [[Iraq Levies]], the [[Duke of Cornwall's Light Infantry]]<ref>''Who was Who Vol. IV, 1941\u201350'' (London, 1980), p. 319.</ref>\n* [[Arthur Turner (British Army officer)|Brigadier-General Arthur Turner]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131952), [[Cricket]]er, [[rugby union]] player and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/21615.html|title=Arthur Turner|work=Cricinfo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Stanley Richmond|Colonel Wilfrid Stanley Richmond]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|MICE]] (1881\u20131962), Deputy Director of Roads in the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War I)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Colonel W.S. Richmond'', 30 January 1962, p.15</ref><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School. Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Henry Cecil Prescott|Lt.-Col. Henry Cecil Prescott]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1882\u20131960), Inspector of Police in [[Iraq]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>Obituary, ''[[The Times]]'', ''Lt.-Col. H. C. Prescott'', 5 August 1960, p.12</ref>\n* [[Guy Sutton Bocquet|Colonel Guy Sutton Bocquet]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1882\u20131961), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref>School of the Black and Red, A.G. Underwood (2010 edition). Hardback p.288: ''President of the OBM Club'' in 1952</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. Guy Bocquet'', 21 January 1961, p.8</ref>\n* [[Brigadier Harold Evelyn William Bell Kingsley]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1885\u20131970), Aide-de-Camp to King [[George VI]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\">''Who Was Who'', Published by A&C Black</ref>\n* [[Charles Hamilton Grant Hume Harvey-Kelly|Lt.-Col. Charles HGH Harvey-Kelly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1885\u20131982), Military Attache in [[Kabul]] (1924-6)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Lieutenant-General Reginald Dawson Hopcraft Lough]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1886\u20131958), [[Aide-de-camp]] to King [[George VI]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Arthur Edward Flynn Fawcus|Lt.-Col. A.E.F. Fawcus]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1886\u20131936), Commander, 1/5th [[Staffordshire Rangers|North Staffordshire Regiment]], 1/5th [[Sherwood Foresters]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School, Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref><ref>Obituary, ''Lieut.-Col. Fawcus, A Fine War Record'', ''[[The Times]]'', 11 August 1936, p.14</ref>\n* [[William Francis Jackson|Lt.-Col. W. F. Jackson]] [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&Bar]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1886\u20131964), Signals Liaison Officer to the US Army HQ in the UK during [[World War II]]<ref name=\"autogenerated37\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=37 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* [[George Croxton Walker|Major George Croxton Walker]] [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] (1888\u20131936)<ref>Obituary in ''[[Times & Citizen|The Bedford Times]]'', ''Major G. C. Walker'', ''Death of a Distinguished Military Officer'', 31 July 1936</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated17\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=17 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n* [[Edward Crozier Creasy|Major Edward Crozier Creasy]] (1888\u20131936), senior liaison Officer during the [[Upper Silesia Plebiscite]] (1920-21)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''MAJOR E. C. CREASY'', November 26, 1936, p.11</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/lifestory/1012374|title=Life story: Edward Crozier Creasy &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Wynn Bagnall|Captain Wynn Bagnall]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131931), [[Canadian Field Artillery]], model for a statue by [[James Earle Fraser (sculptor)|James Fraser]] in [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]]<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XII no. 9 (December 2015),p. 338</ref>\n* [[Melville Rysdale Ten Broeke|Lt.-Col. Melville Ten Broeke]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1891\u20131963), commander of [[Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry|Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry Regiment]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=je2Jz_1c21sC&pg=PA719&lpg=PA719&dq=ten+broeke+vancouver+imperial#v=onepage&q=ten%20broeke%20vancou