pped).jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Tony Robinson (bishop)|Tony Robinson]]]]\n* [[William Edward Toll|The Rt. Rev. William Toll]] (1843\u20131915), [[Suffragan bishop]] of the [[Episcopal Diocese of Chicago]] (1911\u201315)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Thomas Blyth (cleric)|Canon Thomas Blyth]] [[Doctor of Divinity|DD]] (1844\u20131913), author and [[Commissary]] to the [[Anglican Diocese of Ottawa|Archbishop of Ottawa]] and [[Diocese of Niagara|Bishops of Niagara]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Canon T.A. Blyth'', 22 July 1913, p.11</ref>\n* [[Henry Arthur Lester|The Rev. H.A. Lester]] [[Master of Arts (Oxbridge and Dublin)|MA]] (1873\u20131922), theologian, director of the [[Bishop of London|Bishop of London's]] Sunday School Council (1911\u20131922)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''The Rev H. A. Lester'', 26 July 1922, p.16</ref><ref>{{Cite book |doi=10.1093/ww/9780199540884.013.U199273 |chapter=Lester, Rev. Henry Arthur, (died 24 July 1922), Director, Bishop of London's Sunday School Council |title=Who Was Who |year=2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=au%3ALESTER%2C+Henry+Arthur.&dblist=638&fq=ap%3A%22lester%2C+henry+arthur%22&qt=facet_ap%3A|title=Results for 'au:LESTER, Henry Arthur.' > 'Henry Arthur Lester' [WorldCat.org]|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Raley|The Rev. Arthur Raley]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1889-1964), [[Military chaplain|Chaplain]] to [[Royal Air Force|Royal Air Force Command]] during [[World War II]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/7684/?page=7|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - Eagle Magazine extracts &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Thomas Hooton Michael Dix|The Ven. Thomas Dix]] (1908-1985), Archdeacon of [[Zanzibar]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Harpur Trust, 1552-1973. [By] Joyce Godber.|last1=Harper's Charity (BEDFORD)|first2=Joyce|last2=Godber|date=8 November 1973|publisher=|isbn=9780950291703|ocl