mpiled and edited by H. E. Vipan, BA BSc.  Published Bedford by W.J. Robinson, 1900</ref>\n* [[Edgar Mobbs|Lt.-Col. Edgar Mobbs]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1882\u20131917), [[Captain (sports)|Captained]] the [[England national rugby union team|England Rugby Team]] and [[Northampton Saints|Northampton]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Cantrell]] (1883\u20131954), [[Cricketer]]<ref name=\"autogenerated10\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=10 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>  \n* [[Sidney Abrahams|Sir Sidney Abrahams]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] (1885\u20131957), competed in the [[Long jump]] at the [[Great Britain at the 1912 Summer Olympics|1912 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[N. D. T. Oliver|Norman Oliver]] [[Order of Aviz|CavA]] (1886\u20131948), played cricket for [[Bedfordshire County Cricket Club|Bedfordshire]] and [[Brazil]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Henry William Evans|Dr H.W. Evans]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131927), athlete, rugby player and physician<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pcm/articles/PMC2524788/?page=1|title=Dr Henry William Evans, British Medical Journal, 5th November, 1927, p. 850, retrieved July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Gilbert Bull]] (1890\u20131963), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Frederick Charles William Newman]] (1896\u20131966), cricketer<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Dick Stafford]] (1893\u20131912), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Basil Rogers]] (1896\u20131975), [[Cricketer]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Harold Day (sportsman)|Harold Lindsay Vernon Day]] (1898\u20131972), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International who also played [[first class cricket]] for [[Hampshire C.C.C.|Hampshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Maurice Pugh]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1903\u20131986), [[Cricketer]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/14/14378/14378.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[George Godber|Sir George Edward Godber]] [[Order of the Bath|GCB]] (1908\u20132009), rowed for [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] in the [[The Boat Race|1928 and 1929 Boat Races]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[G.T. 'Beef' Dancer]] (1911\u20131991), [[Rugby union|rugby]] player who participated in the [[1938 British Lions tour to South Africa]]<ref>100 Years of the Blues- The Bedfordshire Times Centenary History of Bedford R.U.F.C. (Bedford, 1986), p.41</ref>\n* [[Ken Richardson (athlete)|Ken Richardson]] (1918\u20131998), [[Track and field athletics|athlete]], silver medallist in the [[1938 British Empire Games]]<ref>''Montana Butte Standard'', [[Butte, Montana]].  Sunday 22 November 1936</ref>\n* [[Ian Mantle]] (1920\u20132010), engineer and rally driver<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Eric Litchfield]] (1920\u20131982), [[Association football|footballer]] ([[Newcastle United F.C.]], [[Leeds United F.C.]])<ref>Note on the Author, Eric Litchfield's ''Book of Soccer'', Published by H. Kearthland, [[Johannesburg]], 1965</ref>\n* [[Gordon Brice]] (1924\u20132003), [[Cricket]]er and [[Football player|Footballer]] ([[Fulham F.C.]])<ref name=\"cricketarchive.com\">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/28/28119/all_teams.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|work=cricketarchive.com|accessdate=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[David Anthony Terence Leadley|Tony Leadley]] (born 1928), rowed for [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] in the 1953 [[The Boat Race|Boat Race]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Arthur Coomb|Arthur Grenfell Coomb]] (born 1929), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Dickie Jeeps]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1930-2016), [[Captain (sports)|Captained]] the [[England national rugby union team|England Rugby Team]] and the [[British and Irish Lions|British Lions]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Bob Gale (cricketer)|Bob Gale]] (1933\u20132018), Middlesex [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Geoff Millman]] (1934\u20132005), [[England cricket team|England]] [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Graham Jarrett]] (1937\u20132004), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Peter Watts (cricketer, born 1938)|Peter David Watts]] (born 1938), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Hamilton Milton|Hamilton (\"Tony\") Pierre Matt Milton]] (born 1938), swimmer at the [[1960 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Peter Kippax]] (1940\u20132017), [[first-class cricket|Cricketer]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Andrew David Curtis|Andrew Curtis]] (born 1943), [[Cricket]]er<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/11499.html|title=Andrew Curtis|website=Cricinfo|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Lionel Edward Weston]] (born 1947), [[England national rugby union team|England]] [[Rugby union|Rugby]] International<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Peter Knapp]] (born 1949), [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who competed in the [[Rowing at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's eight|1968 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[John Yallop]] (born 1949), [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who won a Silver Medal at the [[1976 Summer Olympics]] in Montreal<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Neil Keron]] (born 1953), [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who competed in the [[1976 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[James Plaskett|Harold James Plaskett]] (born 1960), [[British Chess Championship|British Chess Champion]] in 1990<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Alan Fordham]] (born 1964), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Neil Stanley]] (born 1968), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Andrew Trott]] (born 1968), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Paul Owen]] (born 1969) played [[cricket]] for Canada<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Matthew White (cricketer)|Matthew White]] (born 1969), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Tim Foster (rower)|Tim Foster]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (born 1970), British [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who won a Gold Medal at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in Sydney<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[David Gillard]] (born 1971), rowed for [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] in the [[The Boat Race 1991|1991]], [[The Boat Race 1992|1992]] and [[The Boat Race 1993|1993]] [[The Boat Race|Boat Races]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Matt Cavanagh]] (born 1971), British national champion at [[Rugby Fives]] in 2004 and 2006<ref>Rugby Fives Association</ref>\n* [[Roderick Chisholm (rower)|Rod Chisholm]] (born 1974), [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who participated in the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in London<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rowingaustralia.com.au|title=Rowing Australia -|work=rowingaustralia.com.au|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Denney]] (born 1975), former [[rugby union]] footballer who played at [[Rugby union positions#13. Outside centre & 12. Inside centre|centre]] for [[Bristol Rugby|Bristol]], [[Castres Olympique|Castres]] and [[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Kelvin Locke]] (born 1980), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Oliver Clayson]] (born 1980), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Jamie Wade]] (born 1981), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Monty Panesar]] (born 1982), [[England cricket team|England]] [[Cricket]]er. [[Wisden Cricketer of the Year]] in 2007<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Richard King (English cricketer)|Richard King]] (born 1984), [[Cricket]]er<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Robin Kemp]] (born 1984), [[Cricket]]er<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cucc.net/pages/players-display-70|title=Cambridge University Cricket Club \u2013 Player Profiles|work=cucc.net|accessdate=30 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226200925/http://cucc.net/pages/players-display-70|archive-date=26 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Staff]] (born 1991), professional [[rugby union]] player who plays for [[RFU Championship]] side, [[Bedford Blues]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordshire-news.co.uk/Rugby-Union-Bedford-Blues-sign-Phil-Boulton-extends-stay/story-21732693-detail/story.html|title=Rugby Union: Bedford Blues sign two more and Phil Boulton extends stay|work=Bedfordshire News|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Julie Rogers (athlete)|Julie Rogers]] (born 1998), participant in the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]] and the [[2016 Summer Paralympics]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordshire-news.co.uk/Young-Bedford-paralympian-Julie-Rogers-appear-BBC-documentary/story-21723953-detail/story.html|title=Young Bedford paralympian Julie Rogers to appear in BBC documentary|work=Bedfordshire News|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/sport/julie-rogers-on-track-to-be-a-hit-after-deciding-she-won-t-play-volleyball-at-rio-2016-paralympics-a3329456.html|title=Julie Rogers on track to be a hit after deciding she won't play ball|date=25 August 2016|website=Evening Standard|accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n<!--- STOP! Be warned that by using this process instead of Articles for Creation, this article is subject to scrutiny. As an article in \"mainspace\", it will be DELETED if there are problems, not just declined. If you wish to use AfC, please return to the Wizard and continue from there. --->\n\n{{DEFAU