{"title_page": "Krsna (rapper)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musician\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = File:IMG 0838 Rapper KRSNA.jpg\n| birth_name       = Krishna\n| genre            = [[Hip hop music|Hip-hop]]\n| alias            = KR$NA, KRSNA, PROZPEKT\n| instrument       = Vocal\n| associated_acts  = [[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]], [[Manj Musik]]\n| years_active     = 2005 &ndash; present\n| label            = [[Universal Music]], [[Zee Music Company]], Ak Projekts, Kalamkaar\n| name             = KR$NA\n| caption          = KR$NA performing in 2016\n| birth_date       = 4 october 1988\n}}\n\n'''Krishna Kaul''', better known by the stage name '''Krsna''' (stylised as '''KR$NA'''), and formerly known as '''Prozpekt''', is a [[Rapping|rapper]] and songwriter from [[New Delhi, India]].<ref name=\"Sridharan 2017\">{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Krsna-Rap-is-about-the-situation-that-surrounds-you/articleshow/37841572.cms|title=Krsna: Rap is about the situation that surrounds you|last=Sridharan|first=Apuurva|work=[[The Times of India]]|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref><ref name=\"Rodricks 2017\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/no-plan-b-for-this-rapper/article6085399.ece|title=No Plan B for this rapper|last=Rodricks|first=Allan Moses|date=2014-06-05|work=The Hindu|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> He is one of the earliest rappers to emerge in the [[Indian Hip Hop]] scene in the mid-2000s under the stage name Prozpekt. He also featured in the 2019 Bollywood film [[Gully Boy]] as himself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/the-4th-episode-of-voice-of-the-streets-featuring-rapper-krishna-kaul-is-here-and-its-brilliant/20353197|title=The 4th episode of Voice of the Streets featuring rapper Krishna Kaul is here and it's brilliant|date=2019-02-05|website=mid-day|language=en|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm10384314/|title=Krishna Kaul|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref> .\nHe known as father of emiway bantai and Chen k\n\n== Early life and education ==\nKaul was born in [[New Delhi]], [[India]] and is a  [[\\|kashmiri pandit]]. He attended [[Hansraj College|Hansraj College in Delhi University]] and subsequently moved to [[Mumbai]] to pursue a post graduate course at [[St. Xavier's College, Mumbai|St. Xavier's College]] and a career in the music business before returning to New Delhi in 2015.<ref name=\"UK 2017\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehiphopchronicle.com/young-prozpekt-indian-prince/2058/|title=Young Prozpekt - Indian Prince - The Hip Hop Chronicle UK|last=UK|first=The Hip Hop Chronicle|date=2008-04-27|work=The Hip Hop Chronicle UK|access-date=2017-12-26|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"IANS 2017\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/krsna-s-sellout-title-track-video-released-114110100337_1.html|title=Krsna's 'Sellout' title track video released|last=IANS|date=2014-11-01|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nBeing exposed to Hip Hop music at an early age, Kaul started recording and releasing songs on his [[MySpace]] page in 2006, by 2008 he had gained a small local fanbase in New Delhi and racked up features with artists in the U.S and Canada.<ref name=\"UK 2017\" /> His first shot of success came with the release of the music video for \"Kaisa Mera Desh\" in 2010,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/desi-rapper-slamming-cwg-is-a-hit/97263|title=Desi rapper slamming CWG is a hit|work=mid-day|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mensxp.com/entertainment/must-watch/3151-yeh-kaisa-mera-desh-young-prozpekts-rant-against-the-commonwealth-games.html|title='Yeh Kaisa Mera Desh: - Young Prozpekt's Rant against the Commonwealth Games|work=Men's XP|access-date=2017-12-26|language=en}}</ref> becoming the first Indian hip hop song on [[YouTube]] and earning a #2 ranking as one of the most watched music videos in India overnight following its release.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/hip-hop-hustle/1/298301.html|title=Hip hop hustle|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref> He also released a song titled \"Vijay\" in collaboration with international NGO [[Save The Children]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title=Young Prozpekt playing for change |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/music/young-prozpekt-playing-for-change/story-Qr1RKZrGhrS8jn9KHFHoPL.html}}</ref>\n\nAfter sporadic underground releases, Kaul switched from Prozpekt to his current stage name KR$NA after signing a record deal with [[Universal Music]] in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/biz/music/artiste/contrabands-signs-indie-artist-rapper-and-hip-hop-musician-krsna|title=Contrabands signs on indie artist, rapper and hip-hop musician - KRSNA|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref> In May 2014, he released his debut album ''Sellout'', an all-English effort on Universal Music with its lead single \"Last Night\" peaking at #5 on the [[Vh1|Vh1 Music Charts]] in India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/node/37851|title=I live and breathe rap: Indian Rapper Krsna|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref> Kaul became the first hip hop artist in India to do a five city album tour with a band.<ref name=\"Rodricks 2017\" /><ref name=\"Sridharan 2017\" /> Following this, the music video for the title song \"Sellout\" was released but failed to make a large impact due to lackluster marketing and shrinking label budgets.<ref name=\"IANS 2017\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicunplugged.in/news/music_news_info/226/0|title=Musicunplugged.in : news|last=Ferreira|first=Verus|website=www.musicunplugged.in|language=en|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref> After a 2-year hiatus, Kaul made his return in 2016 with his Hindi release \"Vyanjan\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/arts/alphabetic-rap-youtube-vyanjan-krishna-kaul-demonetisation-indian-army-caste-system/story/1/14096.html|title=How I made a rap song using the entire Hindi alphabet|website=www.dailyo.in|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thequint.com/videos/rappers-vyanjan-krsna-hip-hop-sellout-universal-music-rap-music|title=Rap Scene Today is Bigger, Less Friendly: KRSNA of \u2018Vyanjan\u2019 Fame|work=The Quint|access-date=2017-12-26|language=en}}</ref> Following the success of song, he signed to the artist management agency DNH (KALAMKAAR) Artists in 2017 and became the partner in 2018, whom he is currently represented by along with the likes of [[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]] and [[Manj Musik]]. As of 2019 he has released some new singles but there hasn't been another album so far.He released 3 Songs in 2020 , Untitled,Maharani and Makasam. All the 3 songs being Disses towards another rapper who goes by the name Mufaad.All 3 tracks were very successful crossing 2+ million views and counting on Youtube .\nHis speciality is that he changes the gender without any surgery\n\n==Discography==\n=== Albums ===\n*\"Sellout (2014)\"\n*\"TBA (2020)\"\n\n=== Singles ===\nF$ck wit us-2008(prozpekt)\n\nGet out of my way-2009(prozpekt)\n\nKhatarnaak-2010(prozpekt)\n\nKaisa Mera desh-2010(prozpekt)\n\nAmped up remix-2011(prozpekt)\n\nPucho na yrr remix-2011(prozpekt)\n\nDisconnect-2011(prozpekt)\n\nLokpaal freestyle-2011(prozpekt)\n\nPeechey na dekh-2012(prozpekt)\n\nPut yr lighters up-2012(prozpekt)\n\nVijay-2012(prozpekt)\n\nCold blooded-2013 (prozpekt)\n\nHow u like me now-2013(prozpekt)\n\n'''The glorious first step-2014'''\n\n'''Faded-2014'''\n\n'''Sellout-2014'''\n\n'''Getting away-2014'''\n\n'''Last night-2014'''\n\n'''Erryday-2014'''\n\n'''Tripping-2014'''\n\n'''Last song-2014'''\n\nBeyond the matrix(prozpekt)-2015\n\nI'm back-2016\n\nNo hashtag-2016\n\nKeep it real-2016\n\nVyanjan-2016\n\nDesi wrap up [[Tel:20162016|2016-2016]]\n\nMeri baari-2017\n\nDekh kaun Aaya waapas-2017\n\nTere buss ki na hai-2017\n\nWoofer-